\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces System context for the precise-alignment stage. The 3DGS model and its SfM point cloud are constructed offline from survey imagery and registered in a global ENU frame. At mission time the SLAM system provides a metre-scale initial pose, which --- together with a live point cloud acquired from the physical vine --- is consumed by the precise-alignment stage. The resulting rigid transform updates the robot pose estimate, which is then used by all downstream manipulation tasks: cut-point detection, arm path planning, and collision avoidance.}}{60}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pa-system-context}{{4.1}{60}{}{figure.4.1}{}}
\newlabel{fig:pa-system-context@cref}{{[figure][1][4]4.1}{[1][60][]60}{}{}{}}
