\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.10}{\ignorespaces GICP perturbation hypothesis scheme. Thirty-five candidate poses are generated by applying structured rigid-body perturbations (Orig and Groups~A, B, C,~and~E; \cref  {tab:pa-perturbation-groups}) to the initial SLAM pose; each hypothesis is registered against the single target point cloud extracted from the 3DGS model. The hypothesis whose registration achieves the highest fitness score above the acceptance threshold (and lowest RMSE as a tiebreaker) is selected as the final alignment. }}{80}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pa-icp-candidates}{{4.10}{80}{}{figure.4.10}{}}
