\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.11}{\ignorespaces Graduated GICP registration loop for a single perturbation hypothesis. Phase~1 uses a Huber loss ($k_1 = 1.5$\,m) for broad alignment; Phase~2 switches to a Cauchy loss ($k_2 = 0.5$\,m) for precision refinement. Both phases apply a rotation constraint that clamps the total accumulated pitch and roll correction to $\pm 5^{\circ }$. The final transformation is composed as $T_{\text  {ICP}} = T_{\text  {p2}} \cdot T_{\text  {p1}}$.}}{83}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pa-graduated-icp}{{4.11}{83}{}{figure.4.11}{}}
