\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.13}{\ignorespaces Pipeline execution model. Each localisation request is dispatched as a sequence of \texttt  {AsyncCommand} objects to an asynchronous task queue, which executes them in a dedicated worker thread pool. The GPU-resident FoundationStereo inference stage is protected by a semaphore concurrency guard; target cloud extraction from the 3DGS model is a CPU-bound read of Gaussian mean positions and does not require GPU access. Incoming requests are queued independently, ensuring each observation is processed in full.}}{87}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pa-execution-model}{{4.13}{87}{}{figure.4.13}{}}
\newlabel{fig:pa-execution-model@cref}{{[figure][13][4]4.13}{[1][87][]87}{}{}{}}
