\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.16}{\ignorespaces Initial pose measurement geometry (top-down view). The approach angle~$\theta $ is determined by triangulation from the vine reference point~$P$ on the mounting frame. A perpendicular from the robot sensor position~$R$ back to the frame intersects at~$Q$; the lateral offset~$PQ$ along the frame and the perpendicular distance~$QR$ define a right triangle from which $\theta = \arctan (PQ / QR)$ is computed.}}{92}{}\protected@file@percent }
