\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.17}{\ignorespaces Per-trial evaluation protocol. The initial pose is perturbed to generate 35 candidate hypotheses (Orig and Groups~A, B, C,~and~E), each registered independently via GICP. Per-hypothesis fitness and RMSE are recorded; hypotheses with fitness below~0.8 are rejected, and the best remaining result is selected. Three complementary validation strategies --- perturbation convergence consistency, inter-trial consistency, and visual overlay --- are applied to the serialised results.}}{94}{}\protected@file@percent }
